2.1 **Grant of Access**: Subject to the Customer's compliance with this Agreement and payment of the Subscription Fees, the Provider grants to the Customer a non-exclusive, non-transferable right to access and use the Service during the Subscription Term, solely for the Customer's internal business purposes.

2.2 **Service Description**: The Service comprises: {{service_description}}. The specific features and functionality included depend on the Subscription Tier ({{subscription_tier}}).

2.3 **User Limits**: The Customer may permit up to [●] Authorised Users to access the Service under the {{subscription_tier}} tier. Additional users may be added subject to payment of additional fees.

2.4 **Restrictions**: The Customer shall not, and shall procure that Authorised Users do not:

   (a) copy, modify, adapt, or create derivative works from the Service;

   (b) reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any part of the Service;

   (c) rent, lease, sub-license, loan, or distribute the Service;

   (d) remove or obscure any proprietary notices on the Service;

   (e) use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in breach of any applicable law or regulation;

   (f) transmit any viruses, malware, or harmful code through the Service;

   (g) attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service or its related systems or networks;

   (h) use the Service to store or transmit material that infringes third-party rights;

   (i) use the Service in any manner that could damage, disable, overburden, or impair the Service; or

   (j) use the Service to provide services to third parties (except as expressly permitted under an enterprise plan).

2.5 **Availability**: The Provider shall use commercially reasonable efforts to make the Service available 24 hours a day, seven days a week, subject to Clause 3 (Service Levels) and Clause 9 (Maintenance and Updates).

3.1 **Uptime Commitment**: The Provider shall use commercially reasonable efforts to maintain the Service with an Uptime of at least {{uptime_sla_percentage}}% during each calendar month (the "**SLA Target**").

3.2 **Uptime Definition**: "**Uptime**" means the percentage of time during a calendar month that the Service is available and operational, excluding:

   (a) planned maintenance windows notified in accordance with Clause 9;

   (b) downtime caused by factors outside the Provider's reasonable control (including force majeure events, internet service provider failures, or Customer's equipment or network);

   (c) downtime resulting from Customer's or Authorised Users' breach of this Agreement; or

   (d) unavailability of any third-party services integrated with the Service.

3.3 **Service Credits**: If the Provider fails to meet the SLA Target in any calendar month, the Customer shall be entitled to the following service credits:

   | Monthly Uptime | Service Credit |
   |----------------|----------------|
   | < {{uptime_sla_percentage}}% but ≥ 99.0% | 5% of monthly fee |
   | < 99.0% but ≥ 95.0% | 10% of monthly fee |
   | < 95.0% | 25% of monthly fee |

3.4 **Claiming Credits**: Service credits must be claimed in writing within 30 days of the end of the month in which the SLA failure occurred. Service credits are the Customer's sole and exclusive remedy for any SLA failure.

3.5 **Support**: The Provider shall provide support services as follows:

   {{#if support_tier}}
   **Support Tier**: {{support_tier}}

   - **Email Support**: Response within [2 business days]
   {{#if_equals support_tier "priority"}}- **Priority Support**: Response within [4 hours during business hours]
   {{/if_equals}}
   {{#if_equals support_tier "24x7"}}- **24/7 Support**: Response within [1 hour, 24/7/365]
   {{/if_equals}}
   {{/if}}

4.1 **Account Security**: The Customer is responsible for:

   (a) maintaining the confidentiality of all user credentials and passwords;

   (b) all activities that occur under its account or Authorised Users' accounts;

   (c) immediately notifying the Provider of any unauthorized use of its account or any other breach of security; and

   (d) ensuring that Authorised Users comply with this Agreement.

4.2 **Acceptable Use**: The Customer shall ensure that its use of the Service complies with the Provider's Acceptable Use Policy (as updated from time to time and available at [URL]).

4.3 **Customer Data**: The Customer:

   (a) is solely responsible for the accuracy, quality, and legality of Customer Data;

   (b) warrants that it has all necessary rights and consents to provide Customer Data to the Provider and to permit the Provider to process Customer Data as contemplated by this Agreement;

   (c) shall not submit any Customer Data that infringes third-party Intellectual Property Rights or violates any law; and

   (d) acknowledges that the Provider has no obligation to monitor or review Customer Data.

4.4 **Technical Requirements**: The Customer shall ensure that Authorised Users have the necessary equipment, internet connection, and compatible browsers/devices to access the Service as specified in the Documentation.

5.1 **Subscription Fees**: The Customer shall pay the Provider the following Subscription Fees:

   - **Tier**: {{subscription_tier}}
   - **Fee**: {{currency_symbol}}{{subscription_fee}} per {{billing_frequency_text}}
   - **Billing Frequency**: {{billing_frequency}}

5.2 **Payment Terms**: 

   (a) {{#if_equals billing_frequency "monthly"}}Subscription Fees are payable monthly in advance on or before the first day of each month.{{/if_equals}}
   {{#if_equals billing_frequency "annually"}}Subscription Fees are payable annually in advance on or before each anniversary of the Service Commencement Date.{{/if_equals}}

   (b) All amounts are exclusive of VAT or other applicable sales taxes, which shall be added to invoices where applicable.

   (c) Payment shall be made within [14 days] of the invoice date by [bank transfer / direct debit / credit card] to the Provider's designated account.

5.3 **Fee Increases**: The Provider may increase the Subscription Fees on [30 days'] written notice to the Customer, provided that:

   (a) no increase shall take effect during the Initial Term; and

   (b) increases during Renewal Terms shall not exceed [5]% per annum or RPI/CPI (whichever is greater).

5.4 **Late Payment**: If any amount is not paid by the due date:

   (a) the Provider may charge interest on the overdue amount at [●]% per annum above the [base rate of the Bank of England / Federal Reserve rate / ECB rate] from the due date until payment;

   (b) the Provider may suspend access to the Service on [7 days'] notice if payment remains outstanding; and

   (c) the Provider may terminate this Agreement on [14 days'] notice if payment remains outstanding.

5.5 **No Refunds**: Subscription Fees are non-refundable except as expressly provided in this Agreement.

7.1 **Obligations**: Each party shall:

   (a) keep the other party's Confidential Information confidential and not disclose it to any third party (except as permitted by Clause 7.1(b));

   (b) only disclose Confidential Information to its employees, officers, representatives, and professional advisers who need to know it and who are bound by confidentiality obligations no less onerous than those in this Agreement;

   (c) use the other party's Confidential Information only for the purpose of performing its obligations and exercising its rights under this Agreement; and

   (d) protect the other party's Confidential Information using the same degree of care it uses to protect its own confidential information, but in any event no less than reasonable care.

7.2 **Exceptions**: The obligations in Clause 7.1 do not apply to information that:

   (a) is or becomes publicly available through no fault of the receiving party;

   (b) was lawfully in the receiving party's possession before disclosure;

   (c) is lawfully obtained from a third party without breach of confidentiality obligations; or

   (d) is independently developed by the receiving party without use of or reference to the disclosing party's Confidential Information.

7.3 **Required Disclosure**: A party may disclose Confidential Information to the extent required by law, court order, or governmental authority, provided that (where legally permitted) it gives the other party prompt notice of such requirement and cooperates in any attempt to obtain a protective order.

7.4 **Survival**: The obligations in this Clause 7 shall survive termination of this Agreement for a period of [5 years].

9.1 **Provider Warranties**: The Provider warrants that:

   (a) it has the right to enter into this Agreement and to grant the rights granted herein;

   (b) the Service will be provided with reasonable skill and care in accordance with industry standards;

   (c) the Service will materially conform to the Description and Documentation; and

   (d) it shall comply with all applicable laws in providing the Service.

9.2 **Customer Warranties**: The Customer warrants that:

   (a) it has the right to use and disclose Customer Data to the Provider as contemplated by this Agreement;

   (b) Customer Data does not and will not infringe any third-party rights or violate any applicable law; and

   (c) it shall comply with all applicable laws in its use of the Service.

9.3 **DISCLAIMER**: EXCEPT AS EXPRESSLY PROVIDED IN THIS AGREEMENT:

   (a) THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS, WARRANTIES, OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND;

   (b) THE PROVIDER DISCLAIMS ALL IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, NON-INFRINGEMENT, TITLE, QUIET ENJOYMENT, AND ANY WARRANTIES ARISING FROM COURSE OF DEALING OR USAGE OF TRADE;

   (c) THE PROVIDER DOES NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, ERROR-FREE, OR COMPLETELY SECURE, OR THAT ALL ERRORS WILL BE CORRECTED; AND

   (d) THE CUSTOMER USES THE SERVICE AT ITS OWN RISK.

9.4 **Third-Party Services**: The Service may integrate with or contain links to third-party services and content. The Provider is not responsible for any third-party services or content and makes no warranties regarding them.

10.1 **Excluded Losses**: NEITHER PARTY SHALL BE LIABLE TO THE OTHER FOR:

   (a) ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES;

   (b) ANY LOSS OF PROFITS, REVENUE, CONTRACTS, ANTICIPATED SAVINGS, GOODWILL, OR BUSINESS OPPORTUNITY;

   (c) ANY LOSS OR CORRUPTION OF DATA; OR

   (d) ANY COSTS OF SUBSTITUTE SERVICES,

EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES AND REGARDLESS OF THE LEGAL THEORY ON WHICH ANY CLAIM IS BASED.

10.2 **Cap on Liability**: SUBJECT TO CLAUSE 10.3, EACH PARTY'S TOTAL AGGREGATE LIABILITY ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO THIS AGREEMENT SHALL NOT EXCEED {{liability_cap_multiple}} TIMES THE SUBSCRIPTION FEES PAID BY THE CUSTOMER IN THE 12 MONTHS IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO LIABILITY.

10.3 **Unlimited Liability**: NOTHING IN THIS AGREEMENT EXCLUDES OR LIMITS EITHER PARTY'S LIABILITY FOR:

   (a) death or personal injury caused by its negligence;

   (b) fraud or fraudulent misrepresentation;

   (c) breach of confidentiality obligations under Clause 7;

   (d) wilful misconduct or gross negligence;

   (e) infringement of the other party's Intellectual Property Rights;

   (f) breaches of data protection obligations under Clause 8 (up to the greater of [€20,000,000 / 4% of annual turnover] or the maximum fine permissible under the GDPR); or

   (g) any other liability that cannot be excluded or limited under applicable law.

10.4 **Basis of Bargain**: THE PARTIES ACKNOWLEDGE THAT THE LIMITATIONS AND EXCLUSIONS IN THIS CLAUSE 10 ARE REASONABLE AND REFLECT THE ALLOCATION OF RISK BETWEEN THE PARTIES AND THE SUBSCRIPTION FEES PAYABLE.
